### Test Spectra Authentication API with PostgreSQL

# Variables
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7502
@email = test@example.com
@password = Test123!
@displayName = Test User

### Prerequisites: Ensure PostgreSQL is running
# .NET Aspire: dotnet run --project Spectra.AppHost (automatically starts PostgreSQL)
# Or use local PostgreSQL installation

### 1. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "confirmPassword": "{{password}}",
  "displayName": "{{displayName}}"
}

### 2. Login with the registered user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "rememberMe": false
}

### 3. Get current user info (requires JWT token from login response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Test Swagger UI
GET {{baseUrl}}/swagger/index.html
